According to C++ practices, we should avoid global static variables as possible. I think there are 2 options to make the code graceful:
1. Add a UUIDV4Generator class and then make `random_device` `mt19937`  as class static variables.
2. make them as local static variable, like:
```C++
inline std::string generate_uuid_v4() {
    static std::random_device              rd;
    static std::mt19937                    gen(rd());
    static std::uniform_int_distribution<> dis(0, 15);
    static std::uniform_int_distribution<> dis2(8, 11);

    std::stringstream ss;
      int i;
      ss << std::hex;
      for (i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
        ss << dis(gen);
      }
    }
```

