@bramkragten I finally figured out that extra meta data can be shoved into the `description` field added to voluptuous by @balloob years ago.  After combing through the core though, I'd suggest it'd be best to keep this here.

My logic is that we should also be adding this feature when integrations collect usernames and passwords in the config flow.  By my search, there are 237 which collect "username" and 278 collecting "password".  So if it has to be in the schema from core, all those integrations and each auth provider need to be updated (plus new ones), versus just a couple places to transform it in the frontend.

The frontend essentially already does the same thing by deciding whether to mask a field based on its name (i.e. `type="password"`), instead of that having to be in the schema from core.

